Here is a sample HTML code for a professional-looking polling website:
```
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
	<meta charset="UTF-8">
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
	<title>Polling Website</title>
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
	<header>
		<nav>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="#">Home</a></li>
				<li><a href="#">Polls</a></li>
				<li><a href="#">Results</a></li>
				<li><a href="#">About</a></li>
			</ul>
		</nav>
	</header>
	<main>
		<section class="poll-section">
			<h2>Poll of the Week</h2>
			<p>What is your favorite programming language?</p>
			<ul>
				<li><input type="radio" id="option-1" name="poll"><label for="option-1">JavaScript</label></li>
				<li><input type="radio" id="option-2" name="poll"><label for="option-2">Python</label></li>
				<li><input type="radio" id="option-3" name="poll"><label for="option-3">Java</label></li>
				<li><input type="radio" id="option-4" name="poll"><label for="option-4">C++</label></li>
			</ul>
			<button>Vote</button>
		</section>
		<section class="results-section">
			<h2>Poll Results</h2>
			<canvas id="poll-results" width="400" height="200"></canvas>
		</section>
	</main>
	<footer>
		<p>&copy; 2023 Polling Website</p>
	</footer>
	<script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```
This code creates a basic structure for a polling website with a navigation menu, a poll section, a results section, and a footer. The poll section includes a question, radio buttons for options, and a vote button. The results section includes a canvas element to display the poll results.

Please note that this is just a basic example and you will need to add more functionality, styling, and interactivity using CSS and JavaScript to make it a fully functional polling website.

Also, you will need to create a backend system to store and retrieve poll data, and to update the results in real-time.

You can use a framework like Bootstrap to make it look more professional and responsive.

Let me know if you need any help with the CSS and JavaScript code.
